                            <comment id="11853" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 21 Dec 2004 18:38:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Indeed, this fails on Tomcat. The problem is that the mechanism also resets attributes set by Tomcat itself, which leads to those strange NoSuchElementExceptions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;An easy workaround is to specify DispatcherServlet&apos;s web.xml init-param &quot;cleanupAfterInclude&quot; as &quot;false&quot;, turning the entire attributes snapshot mechanism off.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, this has not been fully tested on Tomcat before the 1.1.3 release, just on Resin and in unit tests. The problem on Tomcat has been already discovered shortly after the release.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve already fixed the problem two days ago, for the upcoming 1.1.4 release. In the meantime, please give a nightly 1.1.4-dev snapshot a try (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.springframework.org/downloads/nightly/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.springframework.org/downloads/nightly/&lt;/a&gt;)!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
